  <reg:title>South Coast British Columbia Transportation<in:br/> Authority Police Service Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:amsincluded>[Last amended December 31, 2022 by B.C. Reg. 454/2004 and includes amendments by B.C. Reg. 231/2022]</reg:amsincluded>
  <reg:regpitid>454_2004_pit</reg:regpitid>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e31">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Interpretation</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>In this regulation:</bcl:text>
      <bcl:definition id="d2e42">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>SCBCTAPS-DLEU</in:term> means the South Coast British Columbia Transportation Authority Police Service Designated Law Enforcement Unit;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d2e44">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>SCBCTAPS-DPU</in:term> means the South Coast British Columbia Transportation Authority Police Service Designated Policing Unit;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d2e51">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>transportation service region</in:term> has the same meaning as in the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/98030_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>South Coast British Columbia Transportation Authority Act</in:doc></bcl:link>.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 257/2008, s. 2 (b); am. B.C. Reg. 231/2022, App. 1, s. 1.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:part id="d1e69">
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>Designated Policing Unit</bcl:text>
      <bcl:section id="d2e68">
        <bcl:marginalnote>Powers, duties and functions of the board</bcl:marginalnote>
        <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>The powers, duties and functions of the board of the SCBCTAPS-DPU are those set out in section 4.2 (2) (c) of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96367_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Police Act</in:doc></bcl:link>.</bcl:text>
        <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Regs. 257/2008, s. 2 (c); 231/2022, App. 1, s. 3.]</bcl:hnote>
      </bcl:section>
      <bcl:section id="d2e86">
        <bcl:marginalnote>Geographical area</bcl:marginalnote>
        <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>The geographical area within which the SCBCTAPS-DPU and its designated constables must operate is the transportation service region.</bcl:text>
        <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Regs. 257/2008, s. 2 (c); 231/2022, App. 1, s. 3.]</bcl:hnote>
      </bcl:section>
      <bcl:section id="d1e101">
        <bcl:marginalnote>Repealed</bcl:marginalnote>
        <bcl:num>3.1</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>Repealed. [B.C. Reg. 454/2004, s. 3.1 (2).]</bcl:text>
      </bcl:section>
    </bcl:part>
    <bcl:part id="d1e125">
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>Designated Law Enforcement Unit</bcl:text>
      <bcl:section id="d1e131">
        <bcl:marginalnote>Enactments to be enforced</bcl:marginalnote>
        <bcl:num>4</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>The following enactments are to be enforced by the SCBCTAPS-DLEU:</bcl:text>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d1e139">
          <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>the Greater Vancouver Transit Conduct and Safety Regulation, B.C. Reg. 87/99;</bcl:text>
        </bcl:paragraph>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d1e146">
          <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>the Fare Collection Regulation, B.C. Reg. 190/2012.</bcl:text>
        </bcl:paragraph>
        <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 231/2022, App. 1, s. 5.]</bcl:hnote>
      </bcl:section>
      <bcl:section id="d1e157">
        <bcl:marginalnote>Power, duties and functions of the board</bcl:marginalnote>
        <bcl:num>5</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>The powers, duties and functions of the board of the SCBCTAPS-DLEU are those set out in section 18.2 (1) (d) of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96367_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Police Act</in:doc></bcl:link>.</bcl:text>
        <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 231/2022, App. 1, s. 5.]</bcl:hnote>
      </bcl:section>
      <bcl:section id="d1e172">
        <bcl:marginalnote>Geographical area</bcl:marginalnote>
        <bcl:num>6</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>The geographical area within which the SCBCTAPS-DLEU and its enforcement officers must operate is the transportation service region.</bcl:text>
        <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 231/2022, App. 1, s. 5.]</bcl:hnote>
      </bcl:section>
    </bcl:part>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96367_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Police Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 367, s. 4.2.]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
